h3350_20120502b.patch:
- handles null names;
- removes synchronized from updatePermissionStatus(..); see HDFS-566.

+1 The changes specifically related to this JIRA seem good to me. I just want to understand the cleanups made a little better. Hence, could you explain why the following changes were made?

{code}
-  private synchronized void updatePermissionStatus(
-      PermissionStatusFormat f, long n) {
+  private void updatePermissionStatus(PermissionStatusFormat f, long n) {
     permission = f.combine(n, permission);
   }
{code}

and 
{code}
-  public int hashCode() {
+  @Override
+  public final int hashCode() {
     return Arrays.hashCode(this.name);
   }
{code}
